    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>London</placeName> <date>29th Novr 5611</date></p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>6 Great Alie St. Goodman&#39;s fields</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><add>Hebrew</add></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Revd &#38; Dear Sir&#47;</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">I am quite ashamed of my conduct towards<lb/> you and do confess <add>Hebrew</add> for not replying to your last communication<lb/> to me&#44; as well as for the review of the &#34;way of Faith&#34; and for your friendly expressions<lb/> I feel indebted to you&#44; but sufficient is to express my sorrow&#44; and that an alarming<lb/> complaint was my preventative for so doing to a man of that high esteem&#44; regard&#44;<lb/> &#38; veneration I hold for your high talents and true learning &#40;<add>Hebrew</add>&#41;&#44; ever since I first had<lb/> the satisfaction of perusing your scientific writings&#44; but since <add>Hebrew</add> <date>5610</date> I was attacked<lb/> with a severe cold which gradually brought on an attack in the wind&#45;pipe &#38; which<lb/> actually despaired me causing some alarm till very lately which with care &#38; attention<lb/> blessed be God am quite recover&#39;d&#44; however for the present we must leave further details&#44; it is to<lb/> me a more important subject on which I address you now&#44; With truly painful sorrows<lb/> I have seen in the Jewish Chronicle the place of <add>Hebrew</add> vacant advertising for one&#44; I must<lb/> solemnly declare to you that I know nothing of the matter in any way whatever&#44;</p>
			<p rend="align center">but some time since <sic>learnt</sic> that there were some trifling</p> 
			<p rend="align center">differences but matters would be arranged which gave</p> 
			<p rend="align center">me much gratification&#59; of course this newly advertisement astonished</p> 
			<p>me&#44; now dear sir it has ever been with me a maxim <add>Hebrew</add> but in the present<lb/> case I must&#44; it is most sacred with me <add>Hebrew</add> and as having been for a number<lb/> of years <add>Hebrew</add> of the first Portuguese Congregation in <placeName>Europe</placeName>&#44; also recognized by all<lb/> universities <placeName>Italy</placeName>&#44; <placeName>Germany</placeName>&#44; <placeName>Turkey</placeName>&#44; <placeName>Holy land</placeName>&#44; as <add>Hebrew</add>&#44;<lb/> and&#44; as the descendant of that family which for the last 500 years have been I consider<lb/> myself in duty bound to interfere &#38; settle matters in your favour&#44; after you have served<lb/> them so many years sown the seed of knowledge &#38; wisdom&#44; such an action ought not<lb/> to be done to a great man of your valuable erudition&#44; would my health permit I<lb/> would most willingly cross the <placeName>Great Sea</placeName> to serve you &#38; put them to rights <del>and</del><lb/> <sic>shewing</sic> them <add>Hebrew</add> pray without any loss of time as a brother Israelite&#44; &#38; friend in the<lb/> field of literature reply to my letter&#44; and in the greatest confidence let me know how I can<lb/> serve you and to be of use to you&#44; I beg that you&#44; &#38; they&#44; will give in a little in the existing differences&#44;</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>I have laid before me many important cases from all parts to decide upon <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> and I am not fearful that this will also be one I may succeed <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; they may advertise here but<lb/> they <del>will</del> can only find as <persName>Leeser&#39;s</persName> old shoes&#44; <hi rend="underline">all I say is in confidence</hi>. You may make use of my<lb/> name in any way it can be of use to you. You may mention to a <persName>Mr A&#58; Hart</persName> &#38; another<lb/> gent<hi rend="sup">n</hi>. whom I have seen that application must be made to them&#44; not to be in such a hurry<lb/> and to allow me to address them a truly pastoral letter in your favour&#44; as a true disciple<lb/> of <persName>Aaron</persName> <add>Hebrew</add> and as the son and Disciple of that immortal father acknowledged<lb/> by all in 4 parts of the globe <add>Hebrew</add>. I am determined to serve you &#38; seek this important<lb/> blessing <add>Hebrew</add> and not to be allowed for the sake of a few tempers to <sic>supress</sic> it. Favour me<lb/> with an immediate answer &#38; trust you will hearken unto my voice do not abandon it&#44;<lb/> wishing you with all my heart every blessing <add>Hebrew</add> with all esteem<lb/> I am Revd. &#38; Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Yours very faithfully</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">David Meldola</persName></p>
			<p>It is peace and peace only I seek for&#44;<lb/> trusting that as a gent<hi rend="sup">n</hi>. you will keep a secret such&#44;<lb/> terms which I wrote you confidentially&#59; our friend<lb/> <persName>Hasone Pisa&#39;s</persName> best respects to you &#38; shall be happy to hear from you <add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
